deck: The Josuke Higashikata of the alternate Jojo universe and the protagonist of the latest Jojo's Bizarre Adventure arc, Part 8: JoJolion.
description:
Back Story

Set in the fictional Japanese coastal town, Morioh and sometime after a great earthquake that cause a tsunami (a reference to the Tohoku earthquake) a young man suffering from amnesia was discovered by a girl, Yasuho Hirose. The man later dubbed "Josuke" sets out with Yasuho to discover who he truly is.

Physical Traits

Josuke's age is believed to be around 19. He is fit, attractive male of above normal height. A unique characteristic of Josuke is that his eyes and tongue appear to be two separate body parts fused together. Like several Jojo's before him, he has a five point star birthmark located on his left shoulder blade. He wears a classic white and blue sailor naval uniform.

Powers and Abilities

Stands, supernatural forces that bind themselves to an individual, carrying out a symbiotic relationship with that person, defending them and endowing them with their power. Josuke's stand, Soft & Wet,a robotic like humanoid, that along with super strength and speed as the ability to Plunder. Plundering is the ability to take properties of a living being or a object, such as stealing the sight from a human or the friction from a surface.In order to Plunder, Josuke expels bubbles from his birthmark, these bubbles make contact with the target and removes the desired trait. The true limitations of this power is not yet known.

description: Roy the Rooster is the prankster in the farm. Roy regularly pranks everyone in the farm, which makes everyone on the farm very angry and annoyed. Roy's job is to wake everyone up, which he mostly doesn't do due to his laziness and also to take care of the chickens (but usually he flirts with and romantic with them). He once got fired in the TV show "Garfield and Friends" due to him making insults to Orson and everyone else. He is sometimes shown to actually care for everyone on the farm.
name: Roy Rooster

description: Wade is the scared animal in the farm. He has a lot of fears, in fact, the TV show Garfield and Friends, he had a huge file of ridiculous fears such as living radioactive saltines from Saturn invading our tomato soup, pimentos in olives are staring at you, the entire nation of Paraguay is talking about him behind is back and staplers spying on important paperwork so they can take over the world. Roy regularly pulls pranks on him that scare him. Orson is very annoyed by the fact that Wade is afraid of ridiculous fears and tries to reassure Wade that there is nothing to be afraid of, but it never works.
name: Wade Duck

description: Booker is a little chick and Sheldon's brother. He is named by Orson because of his love of his books. Booker is very aggressive to worms as he tries to catch them all the time, but he can never catch them because the worms are always one step ahead. Booker seems to always to end up in sort of trouble or gets hurt trying to catch these worms. He and Orson have a very strong relationship. Orson took care of Booker and Sheldon before they were hatched when their mother left them. He even called Orson "mom" after he was hatched.
name: Booker

description: Sheldon is an chick who wasn't fully hatched, as his legs are the only part of him that is hatched. Unlike Booker, who has the biggest to catch and eat worms, he is more thoughtful and less aggressive when it comes to worms than his brother. A running gag in the TV show Garfield and Friends and even in the comics that Sheldon has a house inside the egg as he has a maid who cleans his "house", a microwave is in there and even can play table tennis in his shell. It is revealed that underneath his egg shell is actually another egg shell on top of the first layer, which literally means he's just an egg with feet.
name: Sheldon

description: Bo Sheep is the twin brother of Lanolin. Bo, unlike Lanolin, is more nicer, chill and easygoing about things. Although he may not be smart, he is shown to be optimistic. He sometimes does not get along with his sister. He rarely gets angry, but could get angry when he falls for one of Roy's pranks.
name: Bo Sheep

description: Lanolin is a temperamental sheep. She is known to be aggressive to everyone, mostly to Roy because of his prank's he pulls on her. She has a very big mouth as she is very loud and can actually take control of Roy when he becomes annoying. She regularly bickers with her brother, but they always make up for it. She is sometimes shown to care for Bo and Orson, such as when Bo left the farm to stay away from her, she came back to fetch him.
name: Lanolin Sheep

description: Filbert is an intelligent worm. He is the main worm the Booker chases. He usually outsmarts Booker, like one time he put a hose inside his hole so when Booker tried to get him he ended up being blown out of the hole. He usually gets help from his friends and lives with his wife and son and some of his family members.
name: Filbert
